            "body_en": "Open your Airtable base and then click on the CMS-page-builder tab. This is where all your website content lives.\n\nWhen editing, we recommend you open your Airtable base in one browser and your website in another so you can see changes as you make them. Similar to Squarespace or Wordpress, any changes you make in the Airtable base will show up on the website once you refresh the page.\n\nEach row or set of rows represents a piece of your website. It'll be pre-configured with some basic content and tags. Customize the copy, replace images, and add new sections or pages. For detailed instructions on how to build your site, view the [Documentation.][1]\n\n  [1]: https://cms.neighborexpress.org/documentation\n",
